==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Slicker
<hw>Slick"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>That which makes
smooth or sleek.</def> Specifically: <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A kind of
burnisher for leather.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <fld>(Founding)</fld> <def>A
curved tool for smoothing the surfaces of a mold after the withdrawal of
the pattern.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slicker</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Slicker
<hw>Slick"er</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A waterproof coat.</def>
<mark>[Western U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slicking</ent>⟦br⟧
